<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="713" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 894.001YS/27.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Emperor</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kyoto, Japan</hi></placeName>, [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1915-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1915-11-10T00:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>; <hi rend="italic">Received November
                                    12, 1915</hi>.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I sincerely thank you for the kind congratulations on the ceremonies of
                            my accession to the Throne. At the same time I reciprocate my best
                            wishes for your personal welfare and for the invariability of the
                            friendship which united by the bond of amicable relation subsisting
                            between our two countries.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Yoshihito.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>